                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.4731/102: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Sydney</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-15T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 15, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 10, 5 p.m. My May 5, 2 p.m., apparently garbled. I stated “American
                    interests (not imports) have suffered”, meaning transportation interests, of
                    course. The fundamental issue is diversion of traffic.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
